        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St Louis</placeName>
                <date>April 8<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1851</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">You will please send<lb/> me a list of all subscribers for the
                Occident<lb/> in this city and the amt. of subscription due<lb/> from each, as
                without that I shall never<lb/> succeed to collect enough to make a remittance<lb/>
                because some dispute the amt they owe<lb/> and others of their being
                subscribers<lb/> at all, however I think I shall<lb/> be able to collect enough to
                make<lb/> a small remittance as soon as you<lb/> will send me the extract—</p>
            <p>As to <persName>Mr. Hirshfeld</persName>, he told me some<lb/> time ago that he will
                send it himself<lb/> for the <add>חמץ</add>. You will do well to write<lb/> to him
                about it, address in care<lb/> of <persName>Mssr Abrahams &amp; Co</persName>
                here.</p>
            <p>Your prospectus I have got, but<lb/> no subscribers.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">in hope that you are well<lb/> and soon to receive that letter</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I remain</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Your Respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">A J Satz</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <addressee>Rev: Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <placeName>Pa</placeName>
            </p>
